# Security Standards

## Secrets
- NEVER hardcode API keys, passwords, or tokens in source code
- NEVER commit `.env`, `.env.backup`, `.env.bak`, or `credentials.json`
- All secrets must be environment variables set in Railway dashboard
- JWT secrets warn (not crash) if default values are used in production

## Auth
- RIA auth: bcrypt password hashing via `backend/api/auth.py`
- Demo credentials hint: only show in `import.meta.env.DEV` mode
- Mock API keys displayed in UI must be masked: `edge_sk_live_••••••••`

## HTTP Security Headers
`backend/app.py` middleware adds these to all responses:
- `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`
- `X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN`
- `X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block`
- `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`
- `Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()`

## CORS
- Explicit origin list — no `*` wildcards
- `RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN` appended automatically if set
- Dev origins: `localhost:5173`, `localhost:3000`
